hildcare</h2>\n\n<p>The childcare provider must be registered with Ofsted. If the child needs specialist childcare, the provider must also be on the Care Quality Commission&rsquo;s register for specialist provision.</p>\n\n<p>If you want a relative to get Care to Learn for looking after your child they also need to be both:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>providing registered childcare for children they&rsquo;re not related to</li>\n  <li>living apart from you and your child</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Type of course</h2>\n\n<p>Care to Learn is only available for courses in England that have some public funding.</p>\n\n<p>This includes courses that take place in:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>schools</li>\n  <li>school 6th forms</li>\n  <li>6th form colleges</li>\n  <li>other colleges and learning providers, including Foundation Learning</li>\n  <li>your community at Children’s Centres</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Who can&rsquo;t get Care to Learn</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;re not eligible for Care to Learn if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re an apprentice who gets a salary</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re doing a higher education course at university </li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/care-to-learn/how-to-claim","slug":"how-to-claim","order":4,"title":"How to claim","body":"<p>You need to complete an application form each year you want to claim.</p>\n\n<p>You must apply within 28 days of starting your course so that your childcare provider is paid from the beginning of your course.</p>\n\n<p>If you apply after that, your childcare provider will only be paid from the beginning of the week that your application was received.</p>\n\n<p>You can get an application pack by calling the Learner Support helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Learner Support helpline</strong><br />\n0800 121 8989</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Give the details of your support worker if you have one. The Learner Support Service might need to contact them.</p>\n\n<h2>Where to send the form</h2>\n\n<p>A pre-paid envelope comes with the 