household income (parents’ or partner’s income plus yours) and when you start your course.</p>\n\n<p>The grant is paid into your bank account at the start of term</p>\n\n<p>You can’t apply if you’re a part-time or an <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> student </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Full-time student – household income</th>\n      <th>Maintenance Grant per year</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£25,000 or less</td>\n      <td>£2,984</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£25,001- £50,695</td>\n      <td>£50 to £2,983</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Over £50,695</td>\n      <td>No grant</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Course Grant for living costs</h2>\n\n<p>You can apply if you&rsquo;re a part-time UK or <abbr title=\"European Union\">EU</abbr> students.</p>\n\n<p>The grant depends on your household income (your parents’ or partner’s plus yours) </p>\n\n<p>The grant is paid directly into your account at the start of term </p>\n\n<p>Full-time students can’t apply </p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Part-time student household income</th>\n      <th>Course Grant per year</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>up to £26,029</td>\n      <td>£265</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>£26,030 to £28,065</td>\n      <td>£50 to £264</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Over £28,065</td>\n      <td>No grant</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Extra help</h2>\n<p>You might also be able to get: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/extra-money-pay-university\" title=\"scholarships and bursaries\">scholarships and bursaries</a>  from your college or university, eg if you&rsquo;re on a low income</li>\n  <li>extra help for students with children: a <a href=\"/childcare-grant\" title=\"Childcare Grant\">Childcare Grant</a> or a <a href=\"/parents-learning-allowance\" title=\"parents' learning allowance\">Parents&rsquo; Learning Allowance</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/disabled-students-allowances-dsas\" title=\"Disabled Students' Allowances\">Disabled Students&rsquo; Allowances</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"nhs-bursaries\" title=\"NHS bursaries\">NHS bursaries</a> for medical students </li>\n  <li><a href=\"/social-work-bursaries\" title=\"social work bursaries\">Social work bursaries</a> </li>\n  <li><a href=\"/access-to-learning-fund\" title=\"Access to Learning Fund\">Access to Learning Fund</a> if you&rsquo;re on a low income</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Repayments</h2>\n<p>Your payments are linked to your income. You only make repayments when your income is over £15,795 a year.</p>\n\n<p>Each month you pay back 9% of any income over £15,795.</p>\n\n<div class=\"example\">\n<p><strong>Example</strong> </p>\n\n<p>You earn £18,000. This is £2,205 over the £15,795 threshold.</p>\n\n<p>You repay 9% of £2,205 = £198 per year, or £16 per month</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The Student Loans Company has <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.studentloanrepayment.co.uk/portal/page?_pageid=93,6678408&amp;_dad=portal&amp;_schema=PORTAL#tab2\" title=\"detailed information on student finance repayments\">detailed information on repayments.</a></p>\n\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-30T14:44:57+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Student finance and loans","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education%2Fstudent-finance.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Including loans, bursaries, grants, student finance and paying back loans","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=education%2Fstudent-finance","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/education/student-finance"},"parent":{"title":"Education and learning","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/education.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Get help if you&#39;re at school, planning to go on to further or higher education, looking for training or interested in a student or career development loan.","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=educatio